## Deploy on Railway

1. On railway.app, create a New Project > Deploy from GitHub repo.
2. Railway detects Python from requirements.txt and uses the start command
   in railway.json (gunicorn app:app).
3. No environment variables needed - Railway provides $PORT automatically.
4. In the service Settings > Networking, click "Generate Domain" to expose
   the service publicly (your last deploy showed "Unexposed service" - this
   step is what gives you a public URL).

## Project structure

```
pirate-loyalty/
├── app.py              Flask app + /api/spin endpoint (name-hash logic)
